嘿，他们走了？
Hey, where they going?

1226
01:28:12,192 --> 01:28:13,887
他们会回来的，对吗？
They're supposed to come back for us, right?

1227
01:28:13,960 --> 01:28:15,985
我不知道 霍吉，你以前来过这里
I don't know. Well, Hodge, you been here before.

1228
01:28:16,062 --> 01:28:17,222
他们会回来的，对吗？
They're gonna come back for us, right?

1229
01:28:17,297 --> 01:28:19,561
是的，但是从来没有那么远
Yeah, but I never made it this far.

1230
01:28:19,632 --> 01:28:22,226
- 你一定在开玩笑  - 最后一周前没这样练过
- You're kidding.  - Not to the final week.

1231
01:28:23,102 --> 01:28:25,070
他们不会回来了
They're not coming back.

1232
01:28:25,672 --> 01:28:28,937
- 我们该怎么办？  - 好了，听着
- What do we do?  - All right, listen up.

1233
01:28:29,609 --> 01:28:31,543
我们待在一起
We stay together as a group.

1234
01:28:31,611 --> 01:28:34,102
没有人会落下，我们是一个团队
Nobody falls behind. We all stay together.

1235
01:28:34,180 --> 01:28:37,047
有人落后了，我们就跟在他的后面，好吗？
One guy goes back, we get him back up to the front, okay?

1236
01:28:37,116 --> 01:28:38,879
我们是个团队 乌拉
We're a team. Oorah.

1237
01:28:38,952 --> 01:28:40,647
- 乌拉  - 乌拉
- Oorah.  - Oorah!

1238
01:28:40,720 --> 01:28:42,483
我们走，5506
Let's do it, 5506.

1239
01:29:19,225 --> 01:29:21,853
先生，你没事，我是海岸警卫队救生员
Sir, it's okay, I'm with the US Coast Guard.

1240
01:29:48,588 --> 01:29:49,816
再来一次
Again.

1241
01:29:57,530 --> 01:30:00,863
我是海岸警卫队救生员 我是来救援你的
I'm a Coast Guard rescue swimmer. I'm here to help you.

1242
01:30:02,168 --> 01:30:03,465
暂停
Time-out.

1243
01:30:03,536 --> 01:30:04,867
全体起立
Class, pop tall.

1244
01:30:04,937 --> 01:30:07,872
霍吉,出来吧
Hodge, get yourself to the side of the pool.

1245
01:30:07,940 --> 01:30:09,339
是，二级军士长
Aye, aye, Senior Chief.

1246
01:30:12,845 --> 01:30:14,210
乌拉
Oorah!

1247
01:30:23,690 --> 01:30:24,952
冷静，长官
Easy, Chief.

1248
01:30:26,659 --> 01:30:28,422
看来这下吃的还不算太厉害
Guess it was a lucky punch.

1249
01:30:32,165 --> 01:30:33,325
霍吉
Hodge!

1250
01:30:36,169 --> 01:30:38,603
- 你还好吗，长官？  - 你给我站在那儿!
- You all right, Chief?  - You stay right there!

1251
01:30:48,548 --> 01:30:50,277
做的好，查理
Well done, Charlie.

1252
01:30:53,319 --> 01:30:54,684
做的好
Well done.

1253
01:30:56,522 --> 01:30:58,387
乌拉，长官
Oorah, Chief Skinner.

1254
01:30:59,092 --> 01:31:02,220
5506班，“乌拉，霍吉”，数到三
Class 5506, "Oorah, Hodge," on three!

1255
01:31:02,295 --> 01:31:04,195
一，二，三
One, two, three.

1256
01:31:04,263 --> 01:31:05,924
乌拉，霍吉
Oorah, Hodge!

1257
01:31:07,700 --> 01:31:09,167
干的好
Good for you.

1258
01:31:16,075 --> 01:31:17,133
把装备都脱掉
Get their gear off.

1259
01:31:17,210 --> 01:31:19,610
- 快点，都脱掉  - 把装备脱掉
- Go on, get that gear off.  - Get that gear off!

1260
01:31:33,059 --> 01:31:34,424
脱掉!
Get it off!

1261
01:31:38,030 --> 01:31:42,057
5506班，如果我失踪了你们会来找我吗？
Class 5506, will you come find me if I am lost?

1262
01:31:42,735 --> 01:31:44,327
是的，二级军士长
Yes, Senior Chief!

1263
01:31:45,705 --> 01:31:48,333
如果我溺水了你们回来救我吗？
Will you come save me if I am drowning?

1264
01:31:48,408 --> 01:31:50,035
是的，二级军士长
Yes, Senior Chief!

1265
01:31:55,114 --> 01:31:56,877
我相信你们会的
I believe you would.

1266
01:31:57,884 --> 01:32:00,409
我对这个班有很高的期望
I have high hopes for this class.

1267
01:32:07,160 --> 01:32:09,185
我对你有很高的期望
I have high hopes for you.

1268
01:32:12,865 --> 01:32:15,800
马修・斯托克斯，草原城，乔治亚
Matthew Stokes, Savannah, Georgia.

1269
01:32:15,935 --> 01:32:18,267
- 马修，干的好  - 乌拉，长官
Matthew, a job well done. Oorah, Captain.

1270
01:32:19,272 --> 01:32:22,366
肯尼斯・惠特利，清水港，佛罗里达
Kenneth Weatherly, Clearwater, Florida.

1271
01:32:22,475 --> 01:32:24,102
出去要好好争气
Go out there and do great things.

1272
01:32:24,644 --> 01:32:27,374
威廉・霍吉，阿斯托里亚，俄勒冈
William Hodge, Astoria, Oregon.

1273
01:32:28,881 --> 01:32:30,143
二级军士长呢？
Where's Senior Chief?

1274
01:32:30,216 --> 01:32:32,616
他有个机会重返科迪亚克，他就去了
He had a chance to go back to Kodiak and he took it.

1275
01:32:32,685 --> 01:32:34,209
他从来都不想在这里养老
He never had much of a bedside manner.

1276
01:32:34,287 --> 01:32:35,777
他可是条水狗，杰克
He's a water dog, Jake,

1277
01:32:35,855 --> 01:32:38,881
也不是个半吊子的教官
and as it turns out, not a half-bad teacher.

1278
01:32:38,958 --> 01:32:40,323
好运
Best of luck.

1279
01:32:40,393 --> 01:32:43,726
雅格布・费舍尔，科迪亚克，阿拉斯加
Jacob Fischer, Kodiak, Alaska.

1280
01:32:46,299 --> 01:32:48,733
祝贺你，杰克 让我们为你骄傲
Congratulations, Jake. Make us proud up there.

1281
01:32:48,801 --> 01:32:50,268
是，长官
Aye, aye, Captain.

1282
01:32:50,336 --> 01:32:53,271
斯歌特・里夫斯，西斯塔，阿拉斯加
Scott Reeves, Sitka, Alaska.

1283
01:32:53,906 --> 01:32:56,568
女士们先生们，这是你们的毕业生
Ladies and gentlemen, your graduates.

1284
01:32:56,976 --> 01:32:57,965
乌拉
Oorah!

1285
01:33:04,116 --> 01:33:05,913
- 祝贺你  - 谢谢
- Congratulations.  - Thanks a lot.

1286
01:33:07,286 --> 01:33:09,311
- 干得好，伙计  - 好运
- Good job, guys.  - Good luck.

1287
01:33:30,176 --> 01:33:33,168
- 祝贺你  - 谢谢
- Well, congratulations.  - Thank you.

1288
01:33:39,719 --> 01:33:41,050
这没关系
It's okay.

1289
01:33:41,721 --> 01:33:43,916
我们都知道会是怎么样的，对吗？
We both knew where this was going, right?

1290
01:33:44,557 --> 01:33:45,854
只是临时的
Just casual.

1291
01:33:47,693 --> 01:33:48,853
没错
Right.

1292
01:33:52,265 --> 01:33:54,893
去追求你想得到的
To getting what you've always wanted.

1293
01:33:56,836 --> 01:33:58,827
我总想得到更多
And always wanting more.

1294
01:34:01,641 --> 01:34:03,768
好好照顾自己，杰克
Take care of yourself, Jake.

1295
01:34:18,658 --> 01:34:20,956
- 我得过去了  - 好的
- I gotta go to work.  - Yeah.

1296
01:34:36,609 --> 01:34:37,667
再见
Bye.

1297
01:35:52,218 --> 01:35:55,016
女士们先生们，欢迎来此
Ladies and gentlemen, welcome to the Rock.

1298
01:35:55,755 --> 01:35:58,952
我是威廉・哈德利上校 科迪亚克空军机场负责人
I'm Captain William Hadley, CO of Kodiak Air Station.

1299
01:35:59,392 --> 01:36:01,417
- 费舍尔  - 在
- Fischer.  - Yeah, right here.

1300
01:36:01,494 --> 01:36:04,019
米特奇会帮你安排的
Mr. Mitcheltree will square you away.

1301
01:36:04,096 --> 01:36:06,257
其他人跟着克里斯特森
The rest of you, step up here with Mr. Christiansen.

1302
01:36:06,332 --> 01:36:08,300
他会负责帮你们注册
He will process you in.

1303
01:36:23,149 --> 01:36:24,616
真不错
Oh, amazing.

1304
01:36:25,251 --> 01:36:27,048
他不但保持了良好的体型
Not only does he come back in great shape,

1305
01:36:27,119 --> 01:36:28,848
还学会了烹饪
but he still thinks he can cook.

1306
01:36:28,921 --> 01:36:31,082
- 你好，杰克 欢迎你来  - 你过的怎么样
- Hello, Jake. Welcome.  - How you doing?

1307
01:36:31,190 --> 01:36:33,784
- 很高兴再次见到你  - 你们俩关系不错嘛
- Good to see you again.  - You guys keep it warm here, huh?

1308
01:36:33,859 --> 01:36:36,020
很高兴让你知道一顿自在的饭是怎么样的
Glad to know you know where a free meal is.

1309
01:36:36,429 --> 01:36:38,192
我们这个周末在斯特卡需要3个人
We need three crews in Sitka for the weekend.

1310
01:36:38,264 --> 01:36:39,629
你做好准备
You make sure that happens.

1311
01:36:39,699 --> 01:36:41,963
下周二团队会集结
And the stand team arrives here next Tuesday.

1312
01:36:42,635 --> 01:36:45,229
和妻子重归于好了吗？
Patch things up with the wife?

1313
01:36:47,139 --> 01:36:49,835
搞定那个女孩了吗？
You fix things up with that young lady?

1314
01:36:51,077 --> 01:36:53,841
你知道，你还是有机会的
Well, you still have a choice, you know.

1315
01:36:56,215 --> 01:37:00,379
嘿，有个问题我在学校的时候想问
Hey, there's a question I wanted to ask you back in school

1316
01:37:01,153 --> 01:37:02,245
却没有问
and I didn't.

1317
01:37:03,255 --> 01:37:06,383
当你不能拯救所有人的时候
But when you can't save them all,

1318
01:37:08,394 --> 01:37:10,521
你选择哪些人活下来呢？
how do you choose who lives?

1319
01:37:11,997 --> 01:37:14,932
这对每个人都不一样，杰克
It's probably different for everybody, Jake.

1320
01:37:16,035 --> 01:37:18,799
对我来说挺简单的，我只是
Kind of simple for me, though. I just...

1321
01:37:19,138 --> 01:37:23,234
我会带走我第一个遇到的 或是他们之中最虚弱的
I take the first one I come to or the weakest one in the group,

1322
01:37:23,309 --> 01:37:26,972
我尽可能游的更快
and then I swim as fast and as hard as I can

1323
01:37:28,013 --> 01:37:29,571
更持久
for as long as I can.

1324
01:37:31,717 --> 01:37:33,844
大海带走其余的人
And the sea takes the rest.

1325
01:37:38,924 --> 01:37:40,516
觉得我准备好了吗？
Think I'm ready?

1326
01:37:42,361 --> 01:37:46,627
我不再是你的老师了，杰克 我只是你的救生员同事
I'm not your teacher anymore, Jake. I'm just your fellow swimmer.

1327
01:37:46,699 --> 01:37:49,759
这不是我想得到的答案
That's not exactly the answer I'm looking for there.

1328
01:37:49,835 --> 01:37:53,794
如果我觉得你没准备好 我不会把你丢到白令海峡去
If I did not think you were ready, I would not put you in the Bering Sea.

1329
01:37:59,678 --> 01:38:01,942
6030，这是科迪亚克调度中心
6030, this is Kodiak Ops Cent.

1330
01:38:02,014 --> 01:38:04,141
