是的 他的手伤的很重
Yeah, yeah. His arm's hurt real bad.

1366
01:40:49,448 --> 01:40:50,779
好的
All right.

1367
01:40:51,517 --> 01:40:56,580
1号救生员，有两个幸存者 准备放下救生篮
Swimmer One. I got two survivors. It's gonna be a basket pickup here.

1368
01:40:56,655 --> 01:40:57,674
明白
Roger.

1369
01:40:57,756 --> 01:40:58,848
这儿受伤了？
Broken here?

1370
01:40:58,924 --> 01:41:01,722
你带他先走，把他放到救生篮里
You take him first. Get him in the basket.

1371
01:41:02,594 --> 01:41:04,721
我和还有一个人跟在你后面
I'll follow with the other one right behind you.

1372
01:41:04,099 --> 01:41:06,005
- 明白吗？  - 好的
- You got that?  - Yeah.

1373
01:41:05,931 --> 01:41:06,920
- 明白了吗？  - 是的，明白
- You got it?  - Yeah, yeah.

1374
01:41:06,999 --> 01:41:09,024
我这样慢慢带着你，好吗？
All right. I'm gonna lower you down in here, all right?

1375
01:41:09,101 --> 01:41:11,296
- 好的  - 放松，伙计，我抓着你
- Okay.  - Relax, buddy. I got you.

1376
01:41:12,838 --> 01:41:14,169
好的
All right.

1377
01:41:14,606 --> 01:41:16,437
- 你跟着我  - 好的
- You're with me.  - Okay.

1378
01:41:25,317 --> 01:41:27,114
我不太会游泳
I don't swim so good.

1379
01:41:27,252 --> 01:41:30,050
- 你不太会游泳？  - 是的
- You don't swim so good?  - No, sir.

1380
01:41:30,122 --> 01:41:34,081
没关系，我游的很好，我跟着你
It's okay. I swim pretty good. All right, on your back.

1381
01:41:49,875 --> 01:41:53,709
- 等等，我们有小船坐吗？  - 我就是小船
- Wait. Are we gonna take the boat?  - I'm the boat.

1382
01:41:53,779 --> 01:41:55,246
等等，等等
Wait. Wait, wait, wait.

1383
01:41:55,314 --> 01:41:57,874
- 我还没准备好，我不能…  - 嘿
- I'm not ready! I can't...  - Hey!

1384
01:41:57,950 --> 01:42:00,680
- 等等，等等  - 冷静
- Wait, wait, wait...  - Settle down!

1385
01:42:20,072 --> 01:42:21,369
有些不对头
Something's not right.

1386
01:42:21,440 --> 01:42:23,533
1号救生员回到洞里了
Swimmer One's going back to the cave.

1387
01:42:54,673 --> 01:42:56,163
怎么了？
What happened?

1388
01:42:56,942 --> 01:42:58,409
他撞到了木头
He hit a log.

1389
01:42:59,411 --> 01:43:01,208
什么？你在…
What? What are you...

1390
01:43:02,347 --> 01:43:04,178
什么…
What...

1391
01:43:16,128 --> 01:43:18,221
- 他死了，杰克  - 他没有
He's gone, Jake.  - JAKE: He's not.

1392
01:43:20,666 --> 01:43:22,998
他只是撞到了头
He's just got a head laceration.

1393
01:43:27,773 --> 01:43:30,298
我们走，快走
Here we go. Come on.

1394
01:43:32,544 --> 01:43:33,772
我们走
Let's go.

1395
01:43:35,881 --> 01:43:37,143
我们走!
Let's go!

1396
01:43:40,686 --> 01:43:44,747
二级军士长朗道!注意力集中
Senior Chief Randall! Lock it in.

1397
01:43:47,960 --> 01:43:49,018
这只是简单的物理学
It's simple physics.

1398
01:43:49,094 --> 01:43:51,927
只要等着回流就行了，对吗？
We're just gonna time the flush, all right?

1399
01:43:55,667 --> 01:43:56,964
好的
All right.

1400
01:43:57,636 --> 01:43:59,433
你下令吧，救生员
You call it, Swimmer.

1401
01:44:06,745 --> 01:44:07,734
现在!
Now!

1402
01:44:18,290 --> 01:44:22,226
嘿，我知道你很疲倦，好吗 我知道你很累
Hey, I know you're tired, okay? I know you feel tired right now.

1403
01:44:22,294 --> 01:44:24,819
但你得把眼睛睁开，好吗
But you need to keep your eyes open, okay?

1404
01:44:24,930 --> 01:44:28,229
好吗？嘿，你来和他谈谈
All right? All right? Hey, I need you to keep talking to him.

1405
01:44:28,300 --> 01:44:29,995
- 你继续和他说  - 好的
- You keep talking to him.  - Okay.

1406
01:44:30,068 --> 01:44:31,865
军事长 军事长!
Senior. Senior!

1407
01:44:32,938 --> 01:44:35,202
你能帮我把这个打开吗？
Can you open these up for me?

1408
01:44:35,607 --> 01:44:38,337
我要你一个一个给我
One by one, I want you to hand them to me.

1409
01:44:38,577 --> 01:44:39,703
往上看
Reyes!

1410
01:44:39,778 --> 01:44:41,109
他没事
He's fine.

1411
01:44:42,981 --> 01:44:44,710
这里，伙计 这里
Right here, buddy. Right here. Okay?

1412
01:44:44,783 --> 01:44:45,807
- 好的  - 这里
- Okay.  - Right here.

1413
01:44:52,624 --> 01:44:54,353
- 罗伯特  - 我没事
Robert!  - I'm okay.

1414
01:44:54,426 --> 01:44:56,519
他的右臂有骨裂
He's got a compound fracture in his right radius.

1415
01:44:56,595 --> 01:44:58,688
我们试着固定住
We tried to stabilize that a little bit.

1416
01:44:58,764 --> 01:44:59,924
用的这个
We put a collar on this one,

1417
01:44:59,998 --> 01:45:01,625
但只是临时性的
but it's more precautionary than anything.

1418
01:45:01,700 --> 01:45:02,758
谢谢
Thank you.

1419
01:45:02,834 --> 01:45:04,859
他可能有些轻微脑震荡
This one's possibly a little bit concussive.

1420
01:45:04,937 --> 01:45:06,871
我们一路上都在帮他们检查
We checked their vitals the whole way back.

1421
01:45:06,939 --> 01:45:10,102
他们都有些体温过低 但会好起来的
They're both mildly hypothermic, but I think they'll come around.

1422
01:45:12,311 --> 01:45:13,938
非常感谢
Thank you so much.

1423
01:45:17,115 --> 01:45:18,707
不客气
You're welcome.

1424
01:45:22,621 --> 01:45:24,248
这是可能会发生的，本
It happens, Ben.

1425
01:45:25,557 --> 01:45:28,390
不该是我，不该是这样的
Not to me. Not like that.

1426
01:45:30,796 --> 01:45:34,698
我要你在我面前把这个签了
I want you to sign them in front of me.

1427
01:45:35,400 --> 01:45:37,300
你为什么不再考虑考虑呢？
Why don't you take some time and think about it?

1428
01:45:37,369 --> 01:45:38,734
不 这…
No. It's...

1429
01:45:40,038 --> 01:45:43,872
结束了 签了它吧
It's over. Just sign them.

1430
01:45:49,881 --> 01:45:51,075
拜托了
Please.

1431
01:46:15,340 --> 01:46:17,467
每个人都可能出现这样的情况
Could've happened to anyone.

1432
01:46:18,110 --> 01:46:19,270
也许吧
Maybe.

1433
01:46:19,745 --> 01:46:22,908
但是如果再发生了怎么办？
But what if it happens again? What then?

1434
01:46:23,915 --> 01:46:26,577
他只用缝几针就行了，不会有事的
Kid got a couple stitches. He's gonna be fine.

1435
01:46:26,652 --> 01:46:28,483
我们把他救出来了
We got him out of there.

1436
01:46:28,920 --> 01:46:30,319
不，是你救的
No, you did.

1437
01:46:30,956 --> 01:46:33,254
你今天表现很好
You were strong out there today.

1438
01:46:34,660 --> 01:46:36,423
我为你感到骄傲
I was proud of you.

1439
01:46:39,498 --> 01:46:41,295
你准备接下来做什么呢？
What are you gonna do?

1440
01:46:42,000 --> 01:46:44,628
有朋友曾经建议我去钓鱼
Friend of mine once suggested fishing.

1441
01:46:46,338 --> 01:46:48,568
我想我会接受他的提议
Think I might take his advice.

1442
01:46:49,107 --> 01:46:50,335
钓鱼？
Fishing?

1443
01:46:50,742 --> 01:46:51,834
是的
Yeah.

1444
01:46:52,177 --> 01:46:54,645
我们这样的人不钓鱼的
Guys like us don't go fishing.

1445
01:46:55,881 --> 01:46:58,179
我以前好像听说过
Where have I heard that before?

1446
01:47:05,657 --> 01:47:08,922
军士长，你走之前
Senior, before you go,

1447
01:47:10,028 --> 01:47:11,928
我想知道一件事
I gotta know one thing.

1448
01:47:12,564 --> 01:47:14,532
正确的数字是多少？
What's your real number?

1449
01:47:19,250 --> 01:47:21,030
２２
Twenty-two.

1450
01:47:24,009 --> 01:47:25,340
２２？
Twenty-two?

1451
01:47:27,512 --> 01:47:31,608
还不坏 不是200，不是…
That's not bad. It's not 200. It's not...

1452
01:47:31,683 --> 01:47:34,743
22是我没救到的数字，杰克
Twenty-two's the number of people I lost, Jake.

1453
01:47:35,921 --> 01:47:38,048
我只记这个数字
Only number I kept track of.

1454
01:47:56,375 --> 01:47:58,673
把嘴里的海腥味去去
Keeps the sea out of your mouth.

1455
01:48:37,716 --> 01:48:38,740
嘿
Hey.

1456
01:48:39,551 --> 01:48:40,540
嗨
Hi.

1457
01:48:43,155 --> 01:48:45,248
你重新开始画画了？
You started painting again?

1458
01:48:46,224 --> 01:48:48,317
是的，可以有点事做
Yeah. Great light up there.

1459
01:48:56,568 --> 01:48:57,830
你知道
You know,

1460
01:48:59,504 --> 01:49:02,530
那个电话的事我得向你道歉，海伦
I wanna apologize for the phone calls, Helen.

1461
01:49:04,075 --> 01:49:06,475
我该给你空间的
I should've given you your space.

1462
01:49:07,846 --> 01:49:09,677
你觉得忽然出现在这里
And you felt showing up here unannounced

1463
01:49:09,748 --> 01:49:12,342
是最好的办法来沟通那件事吗？
was the best way to communicate that?

1464
01:49:18,523 --> 01:49:19,547
嘿
Hey.

1465
01:49:44,749 --> 01:49:46,148
- 请你…  - 本
- Please just...  - Ben.

1466
01:49:46,218 --> 01:49:50,279
我要你保存它，连同这个
I want you to have it, along with these.

1467
01:49:52,691 --> 01:49:54,181
我签了名
I signed them.

1468
01:50:00,298 --> 01:50:01,526
为什么是现在？
Why now?

1469
01:50:09,508 --> 01:50:12,409
我有…我以前有一次任务
I had a... I had a case a while back.

1470
01:50:12,477 --> 01:50:14,843
你知道的，有一对夫妻溺水了
You know, a couple was drowning.

1471
01:50:17,516 --> 01:50:18,744
但当我赶到那儿的时候
By the time I got there,

1472
01:50:18,817 --> 01:50:22,082
他丈夫正把他的妻子往下拽
the husband was dragging his wife under,

1473
01:50:22,988 --> 01:50:25,218
只是想让自己浮起来
just trying to stay afloat.

1474
01:50:26,725 --> 01:50:29,023
纯粹的生存本能
Pure survival instinct.

1475
01:50:31,897 --> 01:50:33,364
这让我…
It took me...

1476
01:50:35,233 --> 01:50:40,637
让我用了很长时间才意识到 其实那个人就是我
Took me a long time to understand that that man was me.

1477
01:50:45,210 --> 01:50:48,145
哦，可恶的，又来了
Oh, man. Oh, doggone it.

1478
01:50:53,251 --> 01:50:54,411
对不起
Sorry.

1479
01:50:56,454 --> 01:50:58,615
你要接听吗？
Aren't you gonna answer that?

1480
01:51:02,160 --> 01:51:04,856
我不再是个救生员了，海伦
I'm not a rescue swimmer anymore, Helen.

1481
01:51:31,690 --> 01:51:32,987
再见，亲爱的
Bye, baby.

1482
01:52:00,452 --> 01:52:01,476
注意
Lock it up.

1483
01:52:01,553 --> 01:52:04,420
一艘75英尺长的渔船求救
We have a 75-foot fishing vessel in distress,

1484
01:52:04,489 --> 01:52:06,457
在深海区域船进水
taking on water in high seas.

1485
01:52:07,559 --> 01:52:10,722
船失控了有4人在船上
She's dead in the water with four souls onboard.

1486
01:52:11,129 --> 01:52:14,030
抽水泵无法持续工作
With its dewatering pumps unable to keep up,

1487
01:52:14,332 --> 01:52:17,961
现在的问题不是船会不会沉 而是何时沉没
it's not a matter of if this thing is going down, but when.

1488
01:52:40,525 --> 01:52:43,756
绑紧一点 加把劲
Tighten her down! We gotta secure her.

1489
01:52:56,641 --> 01:53:00,771
遇到这样的情况你必须说不
There will come a time when you're going to have to say no.

1490
01:53:02,347 --> 01:53:08,547
当你面对5到20个船员对你说“救我救我”
You'll be facing crews from five to 20, all saying, "Save me, save me."

1491
01:53:09,120 --> 01:53:11,315
他们在等待奇迹
They're looking for a miracle.

1492
01:53:12,557 --> 01:53:14,047
在24岁的年纪
At 24 years old,

1493
01:53:14,125 --> 01:53:17,253
你得想办法成为那个奇迹
you have to find a way to be that miracle.

1494
01:53:17,462 --> 01:53:19,896
一切正常 我们要开始实施救援了
Sounds good. We'll plan our free-fall deployment to the water.

1495
01:53:19,964 --> 01:53:21,693
- 准备好了吗，杰克？  - 是的
- Are you good with that, Jake?  - Yeah, copy that.

1496
01:53:21,766 --> 01:53:24,997
如果我们要把你放下去 只能放在峰头上
Okay, if we have to put you in, we're gonna get you in upswell

1497
01:53:25,070 --> 01:53:27,038
让海浪把你带到船那边去
and let the waves take you down to the boat.

1498
01:53:27,105 --> 01:53:28,970
- 准备好了吗  - 是的
- Are you good with that?  - Roger.

1499
01:53:29,040 --> 01:53:31,406
我们只有20分钟
We're only gonna have about 20 minutes on-scene,

1500
01:53:31,476 --> 01:53:33,808
- 动作快一点  - 明白
- so we gotta be quick.  - Copy that.

1501
01:53:33,912 --> 01:53:37,609
我看到渔船了 2点钟方向，50米左右
All right, I got the vessel in sight. Two o'clock, about 50 meters.

1502
01:53:44,856 --> 01:53:46,824
舱门开启
Cabin door open and locked.

1503
01:53:46,891 --> 01:53:49,359
救生员准备
Pre-rescue checklist for free-fall deployment.

1504
01:53:50,862 --> 01:53:52,261
哇！船刚才吃了个大浪
Whoa, whoa! Boat just took a wave, sir.

1505
01:53:52,330 --> 01:53:53,729
一个人被冲到船边上了
One appears to have gone on the edge.

1506
01:53:53,798 --> 01:53:54,992
他挂在货网上了
He's hanging from the cargo net.

1507
01:53:56,267 --> 01:53:57,791
我们得把救生员放下去
We need to get our swimmer down there.

1508
01:53:57,869 --> 01:53:59,393
电脑显示风速60节
Computer's showing 60 knots...

1509
01:53:59,471 --> 01:54:00,961
别管电脑怎么说了
Going off com.

1510
01:54:01,306 --> 01:54:04,173
救生员准备
Prepare for a free-fall deployment of the rescue swimmer.

1511
01:54:07,645 --> 01:54:09,306
救生员再次检查
Rescue checklist, part two.

1512
01:54:09,380 --> 01:54:10,847
救生员准备完毕
Swimmer's getting ready.

1513
01:54:10,915 --> 01:54:12,974
检查完毕 救生员准备入水
Rescue checklist complete. Swimmer's coming out.

1514
01:54:13,051 --> 01:54:15,042
明白，检查救生员
Roger that. Check swimmer.

1515
01:54:15,286 --> 01:54:18,187
救生员准备完毕，检查
Swimmer's at the door, sir. Checking swimmer.

1516
01:54:18,256 --> 01:54:19,746
准备好了？
Swimmer ready?

1517
01:54:20,425 --> 01:54:22,620
上帝会保佑你的
God help you if you ain't, boy.

1518
01:54:26,498 --> 01:54:28,022
救生员下水了
Swimmer's away.

1519
01:54:36,941 --> 01:54:40,035
救生员情况良好 他朝渔船游过去了
Swimmer's okay. He's heading towards the vessel.

1520
01:54:46,584 --> 01:54:50,076
他切浪切的真不错
All right, he's cutting through those waves pretty good.

1521
01:55:09,908 --> 01:55:12,342
他接近船支了
That's it. He's approaching the vessel.

1522
01:55:12,911 --> 01:55:14,811
已经上船了，长官
He's at the boat, sir.

1523
01:55:20,618 --> 01:55:23,348
伙计，见到你太好了
Man, are we glad to see you!

1524
01:55:35,266 --> 01:55:37,632
科迪亚克调度中心，6034号呼叫
Kodiak Ops, rescue 6034.

1525
01:55:37,702 --> 01:55:39,932
费舍尔到船上了，但是船的情况很糟糕
Fischer's onboard, but vessel is compromised.

1526
01:55:40,004 --> 01:55:42,268
进了很多水，恐怕支持不了多久了
